<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,1214,1384]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,320,1214,1239]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Identification.</emphasis>
Forewing length 9.0–11.0 mm. 
<taxonomicName box="[688,911,1215,1239]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Metalectra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tantillus">
<emphasis box="[688,911,1215,1239]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Metalectra tantillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dark gray forewings irrorated with white, irregular spots and short lines. The forewing lines are present but obscure and consist of the basal, antemedial, medial, postmedial, and subterminal. The terminal line consists of a series of white dots between the veins. 
<collectingCountry box="[1380,1436,1287,1311]" name="India" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing is similar in color and pattern to forewing and has a pair of white bars in anal area. 
<taxonomicName box="[1140,1362,1323,1347]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Metalectra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tantillus">
<emphasis box="[1140,1362,1323,1347]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Metalectra tantillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinct from the other species of 
<taxonomicName box="[493,616,1359,1383]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Metalectra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[493,616,1359,1383]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Metalectra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the Park by the very dark gray wings with obscure white lines.
</paragraph>
